<HEADLINE>
TEXAS GOV. BUSH TO VISIT KANSAS CITY ON WEDNESDAY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
   
 c. 1999 Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush will fly into
Kansas City today to meet with Kansas Gov. Bill Graves and attend a
private fund-raiser for the Bush presidential campaign.
</P>
<P>
   Bush is scheduled to arrive at Downtown Airport at 3:55 p.m. At
an airport media event he will meet with Graves and other Kansas
lawmakers who have endorsed Bush, said campaign spokesman Jill
Foley. Graves and Bush are expected to make brief speeches.
</P>
<P>
   Bush then plans to appear at the Mission Hills, Kan., home of
Adele and Donald J. Hall for an invitation-only fund-raising event,
said former Kansas House Speaker Pete McGill, a co-chairman of
Bush's campaign in Kansas.
</P>
<P>
   Adele Hall recently was listed in a Bush news release
identifying 115 ``Pioneers'' who have raised more than $100,000 for
his campaign. Donald Hall is chairman of Hallmark Cards Inc.
</P>
<P>
   Bush's swing through the area will cap a day in which the
candidate is also slated to visit New Hampshire and Providence,
R.I. In the evening he is scheduled to fly back to his Austin,
Texas, home.
</P>
</TEXT>
