<HEADLINE>
BIRCH TELECOM ANNOUNCES CHANGES IN MANAGEMENT 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By TED SICKINGER  
 c. 1999 Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. _ Birch Telecom is making several changes in
its executive ranks, the company said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Don Goldman, former chief marketing officer and senior vice
president of Internet services, has been appointed chief operating
officer. He will be responsible for the company's daily operations.
</P>
<P>
   David Vranicar, who has been acting as chief information officer
for the past year, will formally assume that title. He will be
responsible for developing systems and processes to support the
company's growing phone network.
</P>
<P>
   Jeff Shackleford, Birch's co-founder and senior vice president
of sales, will also assume responsibility for human resources,
administration and management of the company's 27 locations in 21
cities.
</P>
<P>
   The management reorganization is designed to support a rapid
growth plan, said Birch President David Scott. He said the plan was
the first of many corporate moves that would stem from a recent $60
million equity infusion by the New York investment bank Kohlberg,
Kravis Roberts &AMP; Co.
</P>
</TEXT>
