<SLUG> BC-FBC-UCLA-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WALK-ON FULLBACK GETS HIS WISH
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ When it comes to UCLA and disabled-parking
placards, one player's suspension is another player's start.
</P>
<P>
   That was never more true than at fullback, where Durell Price
will miss his long-awaited game at Ohio State and walk-on Matt
Stanley, a former Columbus resident, will get the start.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's really a dream come true for me,'' said Stanley, who
attended Bexley High School in Columbus. ``When I was coming to
UCLA, I checked the future schedule and saw the game. I was
concerned with making the travel squad and hoping to play a little
on special teams. I never realized I'd be in this position.''
</P>
<P>
   Neither did Price, who circled this game the instant his signed
letter of intent was improperly faxed to Ohio State in 1996; the
snafu freed him to sign with UCLA.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm frustrated as hell I can't play,'' Price said.
</P>
<P>
   Although Stanley lived in Columbus for six years, attended
several Ohio State-Michigan games and knows the words to Ohio
State's fight song, his blood is Bruins blue and gold. Both his
parents attended UCLA, and his father, Steve, and uncle, Jim,
played for the Bruins in the 1960s.
</P>
<P>
   As an oversized tailback in high school, Stanley considered
walking on at Purdue and Pittsburgh and did not receive any
scholarship offers. When decision time arrived, he followed his
roots to Westwood.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's going to be awesome Saturday,'' he said. ``I can't wait
for kickoff. I get to play against the uniforms I grew up watching
and idolizing.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Lineup changes: After Tuesday's practice, coach Bob Toledo
announced three depth-chart changes.
</P>
<P>
   __ Sophomore Bryan Fletcher will start at tight end over junior
Gabe Crecion.
</P>
<P>
   __ Junior Santi Hall will start at outside linebacker over
freshman Asi Faoa.
</P>
<P>
   __ Sophomore Julius Williams will start at strong safety over
sophomore Jason Stephens, who played poorly against Boise State.
</P>
<P>
   __ Tight coverage: UCLA has placed many of its best athletes on
the kickoff and punt-coverage units, and it shows. Boise State had
one punt return for minus-2 yards, and it averaged just 15 yards on
seven kickoff returns.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have a lot of first-line people covering,'' Toledo said.
``Tackling is athletic ability.''
</P>
<P>
   For proof, Toledo cited receiver Freddie Mitchell, who made a
diving, drive-stopping tackle while playing cornerback.
</P>
<P>
   __ Return to action:!of! Hard-hitting redshirt freshman Audie
Attar returns this week from a one-game suspension for fighting.
He'll compete with Williams and Stephens for time at strong safety.
</P>
<P>
   __ What of Roques? The Bruins aren't sure where senior defensive
back Ryan Roques will play when he returns next week from his
disabled-parking-scandal suspension.
</P>
<P>
   Most likely, Roques will replace the weakest link in the
secondary _ whether it's freshman cornerback Joe Hunter, senior
free safety Joey Strycula or Williams/Stephens/Attar.
</P>
<P>
   __ Probable return: After a collision late in Tuesday's
practice, suspended linebacker Ali Abdul Azziz complained of
numbness in his arm and neck. He was whisked to the UCLA Medical
Center, but X-rays showed no fracture or instability. He could
return as early as next week.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-08-99 0102EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
