<SLUG> BC-SAUSAGE-TIPS09-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Tips for cooking
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Cooking sausage is so basic that instructions should not be
needed.
</P>
<P>
   But some recipes give instructions that are wrong. Or at least
not right for sausages such as those made by Kroeger &AMP; Sons.
</P>
<P>
   Unlike commercial sausages from the supermarket, the Kroeger
brothers' sausages, both the fresh and the smoked, are not
precooked _ with the exception of the Cincinnati-style brat.
</P>
<P>
   First, Mike Kroeger says, don't prick the sausages. Flavorings
will just ooze out.
</P>
<P>
   He suggests either cooking his sausages one of two ways:
</P>
<P>
   _ On the grill, brown the sausages over heat then move to the
side to finish cooking indirectly. This takes about 15 to 20
minutes.
</P>
<P>
   _ Put sausages in a skillet with water, bring to a boil and cook
until the water evaporates, about 10 minutes. Then let the sausages
brown in their own fat, which takes about another 5 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
