<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MUSIC-MTV-AWARDS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CLIPS THAT WILL WIN MTV VIDEO MUSIC AWARDS 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By JOEY GUERRA 
c.1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Will Madonna claw her way past Britney and Jennifer?
</P>
<P>
   Will the Backstreet Boys burst 'N Sync's pop bubble?
</P>
<P>
   Will Ricky-mania reign supreme? Or Will Korn steamroll over all
those pretty pop darlings?
</P>
<P>
   These and other burning questions will be answered Thursday
night during the ``1999 MTV Video Music Awards,`` broadcast live
from the Metropolitan Opera House at the Lincoln Center in New York
City.
</P>
<P>
   Actor/comedian Chris Rock will host the party, which will
feature performances by Lauryn Hill, Ricky Martin, Nine Inch Nails,
Jay-Z, TLC, Backstreet Boys, Kid Rock, DMX, Britney Spears, Eminem
and Moby. Scheduled presenters include Madonna, Jennifer Lopez,
Janeane Garofalo, Christina Aguilera, Sugar Ray's Mark McGrath,
Puff Daddy and the ``Blair Witch`` trio.
</P>
<P>
   To help you wade through the endless pool of prepackaged dance
moves and rap-rock heroes, I've assembled this list of the 12 major
categories, the nominees and my predictions. Keep in mind that
anything can happen, and that these aren't necessarily the clips I
think should win (a different story altogether) but who I think
will win. And away we go ...
</P>
<P>
   _ Video of the Year nominees: Backstreet Boys, I Want It That
Way; Lauryn Hill, Doo Wop (That Thing); Korn, Freak on a Leash;
Ricky Martin, Livin' La Vida Loca; and Will Smith (featuring Dru
Hill &AMP; Kool Moe Dee), Wild Wild West.
</P>
<P>
   My prediction: Korn's Freak whips them all. Surprising? Maybe
not. Korn's edgy, animated video was a mainstay on Total Request
Live, so it gives voters a chance to be hip with the kids and flex
some rock 'n' roll muscle.
</P>
<P>
   _ Viewers' Choice nominees: Backstreet Boys, I Want It That Way;
Jay-Z (featuring Ja &AMP; Amil-Lion), Can I Get a ...; Korn, Freak on a
Leash; Ricky Martin, Livin' La Vida Loca; 'N Sync, Tearin' Up My
Heart; and TLC, No Scrubs.
</P>
<P>
   My prediction: Boy-band mania reigns supreme. All of these
nominees are fan favorites, so it doesn't matter how cheesy the
video is. You can never discount Ricky-mania, but look for Total
Request Live favorite 'N Sync to slip past the Backstreet Boys in
this category.
</P>
<P>
   _ Best Female Video nominees: Lauryn Hill, Doo Wop (That Thing);
Jennifer Lopez, If You Had My Love; Madonna, Beautiful Stranger;
and Britney Spears, ... Baby One More Time.
</P>
<P>
   My prediction: Madonna's very shagadelic clip, featuring Austin
Powers, shimmies past them all. There are other chances for
award-magnet Hill to earn a moon-man or two. Pinups Spears and
Lopez may cancel each other out, so look for MTV-vet Madonna to
groove up the podium this year. Yeah baby!
</P>
<P>
   _ Best Male Video nominees: Eminem, My Name Is; Lenny Kravitz,
Fly Away; Ricky Martin, Livin' La Vida Loca; and Will Smith, Miami.
</P>
<P>
   My prediction: Ricky! Ricky! Eminem and Kravitz are lightweights
in the wake of Martin's hip-swiveling clip, and Smith's unendurable
Miami clip didn't make enough of an impression.
</P>
<P>
   _ Best New Artist in a Video nominees: Eminem, My Name Is; Kid
Rock, Bawitdaba; Jennifer Lopez, If You Had My Love; 'N Sync,
Tearin' Up My Heart; and Britney Spears, ... Baby One More Time.
</P>
<P>
   My prediction: MTV baby Kid Rock takes it home. Lopez, Spears
and 'N Sync are formidable challengers with stronger material, but
none has had the backing that MTV has spoon-fed Kid Rock. The
channel made him a star, and this is just another chance to say,
``Look! He really is famous!''
</P>
<P>
   _ Best Group Video nominees: Backstreet Boys, I Want It That
Way; Limp Bizkit, Nookie; 'N Sync, Tearin' Up My Heart; Sugar Ray,
Every Morning; and TLC, No Scrubs.
</P>
<P>
   My prediction: Backstreet's back! The Boys took this award home
last year for Everybody, and I Want It That Way provides just as
dandy eye-candy. Take that, 'N Sync.
</P>
<P>
   _ Best R&AMP;B Video nominees: Aaliyah, Are You That Somebody?;
Brandy, Have You Ever?; Lauryn Hill, Doo Wop (That Thing); and
Whitney Houston (featuring Faith Evans &AMP; Kelly Price), Heartbreak
Hotel.
</P>
<P>
   My prediction: Hill will get to do her thing, thanks to her
old-school vs. new-school video. Brandy and Houston both received
heavy rotation for their respective clips, but Hill is a critical
and commercial darling. This is a chance to give her the praise
many think she deserves.
</P>
<P>
   _ Best Rock Video nominees: Limp Bizkit, Nookie; Korn, Freak on
a Leash; Kid Rock, Bawitdaba; Lenny Kravitz, Fly Away; and the
Offspring, Pretty Fly (For a White Guy).
</P>
<P>
   My prediction: Korn reaps another bout of success. Limp Bizkit
proved its appeal with a frequently played clip, and Kravitz got a
lot of mileage out of his enduring hit, but Korn's inventive video
likely will be the night's big winner.
</P>
<P>
   _ Best Hip-Hop Video nominees: Beastie Boys, Intergalactic;
Busta Rhymes (featuring Janet Jackson), What's It Gonna Be?; Lauryn
Hill, Doo Wop (That Thing); and TLC, No Scrubs.
</P>
<P>
   My prediction: The former Fugees singer doo-woops to the top.
Somebody get that girl a display case for all those statues!
</P>
<P>
   _ Best Rap Video nominees: 2Pac, Changes; DMX, Ruff Ryders
Anthem; Jay-Z (featuring Ja &AMP; Amil-Lion), Can I Get a ...; and Nas
(featuring Puff Daddy), Hate Me Now.
</P>
<P>
   My prediction: Jay-Z bounces up to the podium. The
Brooklyn-based rapper scored a big crossover hit with his party
anthem, which was pumpin' in car stereos all summer long. The video
retains the same feel-good vibe.
</P>
<P>
   _ Best Pop Video nominees: Backstreet Boys, I Want It That Way;
Jennifer Lopez, If You Had My Love; Ricky Martin, Livin' La Vida
Loca; 'N Sync, Tearin' Up My Heart; and Britney Spears, ... Baby
One More Time.
</P>
<P>
   My prediction: Boy-pop battles it out. The Backstreet Boys and
Martin both hit it big with teeny-boppers and older listeners, but
I Want It That Way is the closest to pop perfection in this
category. Look for BSB to take it home.
</P>
<P>
   _ Best Video From a Film nominees: Aaliyah, Are You That
Somebody?; Jay-Z (featuring Ja &AMP; Amil-Lion), Can I Get A ...;
Madonna, Beautiful Stranger; and Will Smith (featuring Dru Hill &AMP;
Kool Moe Dee), Wild Wild West.
</P>
<P>
   My prediction: Jim West is no match for the shagadelic antics of
Austin Powers and his beautiful stranger. Aaliyah and Jay-Z are
just taking up space here, and Smith's clip, though a No. 1 hit,
was poorly received by critics.
</P>
<P>
   _ Best Dance Video nominees: Cher, Believe; Fatboy Slim, Praise
You; Jordan Knight, Give It to You; Jennifer Lopez, If You Had My
Love; and Ricky Martin, Livin' La Vida Loca.
</P>
<P>
   My prediction: Chances are slim for anyone but the Fatboy. If
there were any justice, Cher would take the prize for her
techno-tinged comeback hit and its glittery clip. Alas, Fatboy
Slim's wryly humorous video is just the kind of oddball thing
voters look for.
</P>
<P>
   _ Breakthrough Video nominees: Busta Rhymes, Gimme Some More;
Eels, Last Stop: This Town; Eminem, Guilty Conscience; Fatboy Slim,
Praise You; Korn, Freak on a Leash; and U.N.K.L.E., Rabbit in Your
Headlights.
</P>
<P>
   My prediction: Another heaping helping of Korn. Clips from the
Eels and U.N.K.L.E. didn't get enough airplay, while Busta Rhymes
and Eminem really didn't offer anything new.
</P>
<P>
   _ Best Choreography in a Video nominees: Ricky Martin, Livin' La
Vida Loca; Fatboy Slim, Praise You; Will Smith (featuring Dru Hill
&AMP; Kool Moe Dee), Wild Wild West; and Britney Spears, ... Baby One
More Time.
</P>
<P>
   My prediction: Martin and Smith's moves seem pretty cheesy after
the first few viewings. The Fatboy may coast on the intentional
goofiness of his clip, but my guess is Spear's school-hall fantasy
will get the best groove on with voters.
</P>
<P>
   As for the artsy categories (direction, cinematography and the
like), your guess is as good as mine. It's a bit of a popularity
contest, but my video radar is picking up another barrel full of
Korn on the horizon. Don't say I didn't warn you.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
