<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Where can I find it?
 &HT;    By Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Having trouble finding a particular item? We'll try to help you
locate it. But due to the volume of mail, we cannot track down
every request. Readers whose queries are answered in the column
will receive a blue and cream canvas Buyer's Edge tote bag. Write
us at Buyer's Edge Find It, Atlanta Journal-Constitution, P.O. Box
4689, Atlanta, GA 30302; e-mail us at buyersedge(at)ajc.com (please
include your name, the city you live in and a daytime phone
number);
</P>
<P>
   or call 404-582-7642.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Do they still make Kaboom cereal? My husband has been dying
for this stuff for the past four years. I would love to find it for
him. Thanks so much.
</P>
<P>
   _ Allison Hatfield, Woodstock
</P>
<P>
   A: It's a boom. It's Kaboom! The presweetened puffed oat cereal
from General Mills, which debuted in 1969, is still going strong.
To the delight of kids of all ages, the frosted, fruit-flavored
cereal is shaped like smiling clown faces mixed with star-shaped
marshmallow bits in yummy shades of green, purple, pink, orange and
yellow. Since the 10-ounce boxes of Kaboom are in limited
distribution around the country, you can order it ($14.18 for a
four pack) by calling 1-800-233-5780, Ext. 994. This is for credit
cards only. Or write: General Mills, P.O. Box 5272, Minneapolis, MN
55440-5272.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I have been trying to locate Work Out! Liniment, which was
great on burns (took the pain away). It was also good for sore
muscles and insect bites. No stores seem to carry it anymore. Could
you find it or a similar product?
</P>
<P>
   _ Sandra Moore, Marietta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: We found the real thing for you. Work Out! Liniment,
distributed by D.L. Carr of Plainview, N.Y., is available only
through the mail. Call 1-800-487-8688 to order the 8-ounce bottle
for $9.50, which includes shipping. Three bottles are $17.50 and
six are $29. According to the distributor, Work Out! can also be
used ``for the temporary relief of minor aches and pains of muscles
and joints associated with arthritis, sprains, strains, bruises and
simple backaches.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: I would like to find Dermatone sunblock, which contains
transparent zinc oxide. I saw it advertised in a magazine and have
looked in several drugstores with no luck.
</P>
<P>
   _ Lori Lynde, Dunwoody, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: No more clowning around for you in the sun. The white clown
look of the traditional oxide product is history. Dermatone
Laboratories' new white UVA/UVB sunblock creme becomes transparent
when applied and rubbed on your skin. It's a soothing combo of
nonchemical microfine zinc oxide and titanium dioxide. And this
creme also prevents chapping and reduces the risk of frostbite,
according to the manufacturer. A .5-ounce tin of creme is $3.25 at
Blue Ridge Mountain Sports, 3393 Peachtree Road N.E.
(404-266-8372).
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am looking for Lysol Touch-Ups. They are a great product
for in-between cleanings of my bathrooms. I used to find them
everywhere, but not now.
</P>
<P>
   _ Edie May Phillips, Marietta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Another request: I've been using Lysol Touch-Ups and have gotten
my mother and sister-in-law hooked, but now we can't find them.
They are great for things like pet accidents in addition to
bathroom/kitchen cleanups.
</P>
<P>
   _ Cindy Wilson, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   Yet another request: I am looking for disposable Lysol Touch-Ups
to clean your bathroom, kitchen, etc. Can you help me find them?
</P>
<P>
   _ Linda Biesecker, Kennesaw, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   And a final Lysol request: I am looking for Lysol Bathroom
Touch-Ups and Lysol Concentrate. Stores don't carry these products
anymore.
</P>
<P>
   _ Rebecca Paden,
</P>
<P>
   Marietta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Phew! These Lysol cleaning products must be something special
_ they have such loyal customers. Some cleaners made by Reckitt &AMP;
Colman have limited distribution, and Lysol Touch-Ups fall into
this category. But order a 36-count box ($1.99) from the company at
1-800-456-9477. As advertised on the box, with Touch-Ups you ``just
wet, wipe and toss.'' You can order Lysol Concentrate ($3.59 for a
12-ounce bottle) directly from the company as well.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
