weekends at a McDonald's in Orlando to save money for a trip back
home. He was unenthusiastic about America, brightening only when I
asked what he would do if Kabila ever fell from power and he could
live in Kinshasa.
 &HT;    He said he would definitely go, ``at least for a while.'' But in
the same breath, he admitted that he doesn't ``know squat about
Congo,'' and worries about ever being expected to follow in his
father's footsteps.
