<SLUG> BC-BUNDY-RECIPES-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CUP FOR CUP, THIS IS MOM'S SALAD
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BEVERLY BUNDY 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   While noodling through the Internet the other day (Do you
suppose Michael Dell ``noodles''? Probably not) I came upon a
recipe for Hawaiian salad.
</P>
<P>
   I have news for the Chicago Tribune, which ran the recipe. It's
five-cup salad. I know because it was a staple of my mother's since
the 1960s. And it has nothing to do with the Islands. I spent most
of my childhood in Norway.
</P>
<P>
   However, it is one of my favorites, and I hadn't made it in
years. The recipe on the Internet is credited to Rose Krautstruck
of Chicago. But I know that's wrong. It's my mother's salad.
</P>
<P>
   And the second recipe is for a Luby's Cafeterias version of a
recipe answer-request we ran a few weeks ago. It's perfect for a
potluck outdoor party.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FIVE CUP SALAD
</P>
<P>
   Serves 10
</P>
<P>
   _ 8 1/4-ounce can pineapple chunks, drained
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup miniature marshmallows
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup coconut
</P>
<P>
   _ 8-ounce can Mandarin oranges, drained
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup lite sour cream
</P>
<P>
   Combine all ingredients and mix well (but not so much that you
break up oranges). Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 112 calories, 5 grams fat, 16
grams carbohydrates, 2 grams protein, 4 milligrams cholesterol, 27
milligrams sodium, 49 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LUBY'S SPAGHETTI SALAD
</P>
<P>
   Serves 12
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 pound spaghetti, strands broken in half
</P>
<P>
   _ 16-ounce bottle Italian dressing
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese, grated
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 tablespoon sesame seeds
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 tablespoon poppy seeds
</P>
<P>
   _ 2 teaspoons seasoned salt
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 teaspoon paprika
</P>
<P>
   _ 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
</P>
<P>
   _ 1/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 medium cucumber, diced
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 medium red onion, diced
</P>
<P>
   _ 2 medium tomatoes, diced
</P>
<P>
   _ Parsley sprigs
</P>
<P>
   Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Drain, rinse
with cold water and drain well. Transfer to large bowl.
</P>
<P>
   In medium bowl, whisk together salad dressing, cheese, seeds,
salt, paprika, garlic powder and peppers until well-blended. Stir
in cucumber and onion. Pour over spaghetti and toss lightly to coat
evenly. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or up to 24 hours.
Garnish with tomatoes and parsley.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 342 calories, 20 grams fat, 35
grams carbohydrates, 6 grams protein, trace cholesterol, 478
milligrams sodium, 53 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   (Beverly Bundy is food editor for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Send recipes and requests to Beverly Bundy, Star-Telegram, Box
1870, Fort Worth, TX 76101. Or e-mail to
bbundy(at)star-telegram.com. Include a daytime phone number.
Responses to requests will be made only through this column. Visit
the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
