u w BC-CHEATING-TIPS09-COX     09-08 0153
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CHEATING-TIPS09-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    With CHEATING.
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANTI-CHEATING TIPS FOR PARENTS
</P>
<P>
   _ Focus on your children's sense of pride. Mention the
satisfaction from doing something on your own.
</P>
<P>
   _ Talk to your children early and often. Then they will continue
to turn to you as they grow older.
</P>
<P>
   _ Practice what you preach. Children notice actions more than
words.
</P>
<P>
   _ Assure children that cheating is neither normal nor
acceptable.
</P>
<P>
   _ Ask children where the world would be if everyone cheated.
</P>
<P>
   _ Focus on fueling a love of learning, rather than obsessing
over grades and scores.
</P>
<P>
   _ Don't overextend children in an effort to keep them
``well-rounded.'' Children without ample time to study are more apt
to cheat.
</P>
<P>
   Source: Educational Testing Service
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
