<HEADLINE>
CELEBRATE NEW YEAR WHILE ON EXOTIC TOUR 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By SYD KEARNEY 
c.1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Many travelers are looking for an exotic holiday for their
turn-of-the-century celebrations. And tour companies have responded
with diverse itineraries, many centered around special New Year's
Eve and Jan. 1 events.
</P>
<P>
   Here is a sampling of what is available. A travel agent can
guide you to a tour that suits your tastes and budget. (Fares are
based on double occupancy and do not include air transportation
unless otherwise noted.)
</P>
<P>
   _ Backroads, a Berkeley, Calif.-based adventure specialist,
offers biking in Thailand, hiking in New Zealand and snorkeling in
the waters off Equador. An 11-day tour that focuses on mountain
biking in Chile and Argentina departs Dec. 24. The $3,898 cost
includes lodging, most meals and air fare from Miami. Call
800-462-2848; or access www.backroads.com.
</P>
<P>
   _ Maupintour's eight-day visit to Australia concentrates on
exploring Sydney, where fireworks will explode over the harbor on
New Year's Eve. A tour highlight is a visit to a koala park. Cost
is $4,095 and includes lodging, most meals and air transportation
from Los Angeles. Maupintour offers 16 other millennium tours,
including trips to Paris, Machu Picchu and Rio de Janeiro. Call
800-255-4266.
</P>
<P>
   _ Saga Holidays, which specializes in vacations for age 50-plus
travelers, offers a variety of tour destinations, including Malta,
Bali and Spain's Costa del Sol. A 16-day stay at an all-inclusive
resort in the Canary Islands costs $2,449. That price covers air
transportation from Dallas, a city tour of Santa Cruz on the island
of Tenerife, most meals and special events. At the resort, an open
bar provides free wine, beer, liquor, soft drinks and bottled water
11 a.m.-11 p.m. daily; the resort also boasts live music and
dancing most nights. Call 800-921-9291.
</P>
<P>
   _ Globus offers a sampling of the Orient with a 12-day tour to
Singapore, Bangkok and Hong Kong, where participants will celebrate
the new year. Prices start at $1,710, which includes air fare from
Los Angeles, lodging and some meals. Contact a travel agent.
</P>
<P>
   _ Houston-based Remarkable Journeys takes holiday travelers to
Mexico for an eight-day adventure highlighted by a train ride
through the Copper Canyon. The $1,019 cost covers transportation
within Mexico, lodging, most meals and day hikes. Call
713-721-2517; or access www.remjourneys.com.
</P>
<P>
   _ Go on safari this New Year's Day with Thomson Family
Adventures, whose 13-day tour of Tanzania departs Dec. 23. The
educational holiday is family-friendly with game drives, nature
hikes and visits to African villages. The $6,500 cost includes air
fare from New York, lodging, all meals, guides and recreational
programs. Discounts are offered for travelers age 17 and younger.
Minimum age for this safari is 6. Call 800-262-6255; or access
www.familyadventures.com. &QL; 
 &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
