<HEADLINE>
MILLENNIUM ON THE HIGH SEAS 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By HARRY SHATTUCK 
c.1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Vacations at sea take on a new dimension this New Year's season.
</P>
<P>
   Among itinerary highlights:
</P>
<P>
   _ Ships representing Crystal, Radisson Seven Seas, Silversea,
Princess and Royal Caribbean will cross the international date line
in the South Pacific as the new millennium begins.
</P>
<P>
   _ Orient Lines and Special Expeditions vessels are destined for
Antarctica.
</P>
<P>
   _ Cunard and Princess plan cruises to the Holy Land.
</P>
<P>
   _ The CostaRiviera will combine ports in Israel and Egypt with
calls in Greece, Italy and Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
   _ Norwegian, Princess and Royal Olympic offer South America
itineraries.
</P>
<P>
   _ A Clipper ship will circumnavigate New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
   _ A Holland America vessel offers Margarita Island and Trinidad
in the southern Caribbean.
</P>
<P>
   _ Seabourn's plans include Singapore.
</P>
<P>
   _ Classical Cruises passengers will take a land excursion to the
Taj Mahal to greet the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
   _ Two Royal Caribbean ships will sail under San Francisco's
Golden Gate Bridge at midnight on New Year's Eve.
</P>
<P>
   _ Two Bergen Line ships will gather at Honningsvag, Norway, for
a celebration at the North Cape.
</P>
<P>
   _ Three Premier vessels will rendezvous in Gatun Lake as part of
a Panama Canal sailing.
</P>
<P>
   _ Windstar passengers will tour Costa Rica and the Virgin
Islands.
</P>
<P>
   _ Temptress Adventures will combine land-sea explorations of
Panama and Costa Rica.
</P>
<P>
   _ Three Celebrity ships will gather off the private Caribbean
island of Labadee for a gala fireworks display.
</P>
<P>
   Entertainment is high on the agenda, too:
</P>
<P>
   _ Travelers booking Silversea's Silver Cloud will gather in Los
Angeles on Dec. 21 for a private concert by Tony Bennett, then will
take chartered aircraft to Tahiti to board the ship for a 15-day
voyage to Auckland, New Zealand. Performers and lecturers en route
(or on the Silver Wind from Cairns, Australia, to Tahiti) will
include Rita Moreno, Joel Grey, Buzz Aldrin, Andrew Morton, Winston
S. Churchill, Mike Stoller, Richard Sherman and Sha Na Na.
</P>
<P>
   _ Joining Cunard's QE2 for a Caribbean/Panama Canal sailing will
be singer Jack Jones, the Jimmy Dorsey orchestra and the Pied
Pipers. On a round-trip trans-Atlantic sailing, that line's Caronia
(formerly the Vistafjord) will feature singer Cleo Laine and
composer-musician husband John Dankworth and actress Liliane
Montevecchi.
</P>
<P>
   _ Entertainers aboard Carnival ships in the Caribbean will
include singers Shirley Jones (Holiday), John Davidson
(Imagination) and Florence Henderson (Fascination) and comedians
Alan King (Jubilee), David Brenner (Fantasy), Richard Jeni
(Inspiration) and George Wallace (Celebration and Tropicale).
</P>
<P>
   _ Holland America vessels also will feature King (on the Noordam
and Westerdam in the Caribbean) plus singer and classical guitarist
Charo (on the Statendam to Hawaii) and comedian Red Buttons (aboard
the Ryndam on a Panama Canal sailing).
</P>
<P>
   Other lines will offer entertainment, but not all lineups have
not been announced.
</P>
<P>
   A travel agent can provide brochures, prices and complete
itineraries, and make reservations.
</P>
<P>
