<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Sept. 9 and thereafter. The stories will carry the ``f''
financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For questions
about stories, contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News, (818)
713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   SUPERIOR-SUIT (CALABASAS, Calif.) _ Superior National Insurance
Group has filed a contract fraud suit against two reinsurance
companies, seeking $200 million in damages. By Dave McNary.
</P>
<P>
   MINDSPRING-SURVEY (Los Angeles) _ MindSpring, one of the
nation's fastest growing Internet service providers, ranked highest
in overall customer satisfaction among the largest national ISPs,
according to a survey released Wednesday by J.D. Power and
Associates. But what's more surprising is who ranked below average:
industry powerhouse America Online and its subsidiary, CompuServe.
By Dave McNary.
</P>
