<SLUG> BC-KIDS:MOVIES:DOG-OF-FLANDERS-CLASSACTS-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MOVIE REVIEW: ``A DOG OF FLANDERS'' 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 By MICHAEL THOMAS, Middle School Student Reporter 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``A DOG OF FLANDERS''
</P>
<P>
   Starring: Jack Warden, Jeremy James Kissner, Jesse James, Jon
Voight and Cheryl Ladd.
</P>
<P>
   Plot: Don't let the title fool you. This movie is not about a
dog, it's about Nello, an orphan boy who finds a dog beaten in a
field and nurses it back to health.
</P>
<P>
   Nello has one great talent: He loves to draw. When Nello meets
the town's most famous artist, Michel La Grande, they quickly
become friends.
</P>
<P>
   But things go bad when the boy is accused of causing a fire.
Nello decides to enter an art contest in the hopes of winning
enough prize money to pay off a mean landlord and save his
grandpa's house.
</P>
<P>
   Comments: This is a movie for people who like art and are
interested in famous artists. In the beginning, too much of the
plot is given away so viewers know what's going to happen, but I
loved the movie. I felt connected to Nello, and even though he was
poor and bad things happened to him, he still didn't give up on
life.
</P>
<P>
   Rating and reason for rating: PG for language, violence and
animal cruelty.
</P>
<P>
   Reviewer's 1 - 10 rating: 9.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
