<P>
   (NYT35) NEW YORK -- Sept. 8, 1999 -- TEN-USOPEN-5, 09-08 -- No.
5 seed Mary Pierce of France reacts after losing a point against
defending champion and No. 2 seed Lindsay Davenport during their
match at the U.S. Open on Wednesday. The American saved two match
points and then came out attacking after a 70-minute rain delay to
beat Pierce, 6-2, 3-6, 7-5 to reach the semifinals. (Barton
Silverman/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT34) NEW YORK -- Sept. 8, 1999 -- TEN-DAVIS-MCENROE-2, 09-08
-- John McEnroe thoughtfully examining the Davis Cup at a U.S. Open
press conference Wednesday. McEnroe, the former world No. 1 who was
perhaps the most successful player in Davis Cup history, got his
wish Wednesday when he was appointed captain of a U.S. team that
has not won the title since 1995. ``It's one of the proudest
moments of my life,'' he says. (Barton Silverman/New York Times
Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT33) ATLANTA -- Sept. 8, 1999 -- AIDS-DRUGS, 09-08 -- Pandora
Singleton, executive director of Project Azuka, near the site of
the 1999 National H.I.V. Prevention Conference last month in
Atlanta. Six years ago, when Pandora Singleton founded a support
group for H.I.V.- positive women in Savannah, Ga., drug executives
rarely knocked on her door to offer financing or information about
the virus. All that has changed. (Alan S. Weiner/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT32) NEW YORK -- Sept. 8, 1999 -- NINES, 09-08 -- On
Thursday, the ninth day, of the ninth month, of the ninety-ninth
year, the date will seem like there are nine's everywhere. A
selection of nine's from around New York City, spelling out 9-9-99.
(New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT31) NEW YORK -- Sept. 8, 1999 -- TEN-USOPEN-4, 09-08 --
Defending champion and No. 2 seed Lindsay Davenport (on the far
