<P>
   (NYT3) BALTIMORE -- Sept. 8, 1999 -- CIR-EBAY-LIVING-1, 09-08 --
Fred Parks in his studio last week. For eight years, Parks sold all
manner of antiques and collectibles from several stores in
Baltimore. Now, he has lowered his expenses and increased profits
by selling exclusively on Ebay, the online auction house. More and
more people are making a living from on-line auctions, often
closing their brick-and-mortar stores or quitting jobs to vend
bric-a-brac electronically at auctions like the ones at Ebay,
Amazon.com and Yahoo. (Ann Grillo/New York Times Photo)
