<SLUG> BC-FBC-UCLA-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
INJURED FARMER EXPECTS TO SEE LIMITED PLAYING TIME
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Injured receiver Danny Farmer has made significant
progress this week and is expected to play Saturday at Ohio State.
How much _ and how well _ remains to be seen.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a big game and my ankle's ready,'' said Farmer, who
sprained his left ankle during a scrimmage Aug. 21. ``I've been
listening to it and I've been careful.''
</P>
<P>
   A preseason All-American, Farmer suffered a high sprain (above
the ankle bone), which takes longer to heal than conventional low
sprains. He spent one week on crutches and another wearing a
protective boot.
</P>
<P>
   Although it might have seemed excessive _ after all, he walked
off the field immediately after the injury _ he now believes the
crutches and boot were essential to his recovery.
</P>
<P>
   Officially he's listed as probable, and if a setback occurs
today or Friday, he won't play.
</P>
<P>
   ``The trainers did a great job,'' he said. ``Now, I could go in
and not be able to play. Or I could go in and feel 100 percent.
We'll have to see.''
</P>
<P>
   The coaches will avoid using Farmer for pass patterns that put
unnecessary strain on his ankle.
</P>
<P>
   ``We'll try to script some things that he can run and feel good
about,'' coach Bob Toledo said. ``He won't play the whole game.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Redshirt update: Six freshmen played against Boise State:
tight end Mike Seidman, offensive tackle Bryce Bohlander,
cornerback Ricky Manning, linebackers Asi Faoa and Marcus Reese and
punter/kicker Nathan Fikse.
</P>
<P>
   That leaves just 10 freshmen with a chance to redshirt. The
other members of UCLA's 18-man recruiting class are quarterback
J.P. Losman, who transferred, and cornerback DeShaun McCullough,
who has not enrolled for academic reasons.
</P>
<P>
   Coach Bob Toledo also hopes to redshirt sophomore receiver Jon
Dubravac, who did not play against Boise State.
</P>
<P>
   __ Signs of life: After a lackluster training camp, the 11
suspended players are practicing with increased enthusiasm as their
return to action approaches.
</P>
<P>
   ``They've been much more intense, maybe because I told them I
wasn't real happy with how they were working,'' Toledo said.
</P>
<P>
   There's no guarantee the suspended players will start upon their
return next week. If the replacements play well at Ohio State,
Toledo said, they'll have a chance to start against Fresno State.
</P>
<P>
   __ Holding on: Four players from last year's team are on NFL
rosters: quarterback Cade McNown (Chicago), safety Larry Atkins
(Kansas City), offensive lineman Kris Farris (Pittsburgh, injured
reserve) and tight end Ryan Neufeld (Dallas, practice squad).
</P>
<P>
   Chris Sailer (San Francisco), Craig Walendy (San Francisco),
Mike Grieb (San Francisco), Brendon Ayanbadejo (Atlanta) and Andy
Meyers (Buffalo) have been cut.
</P>
<P>
   __ Parking scandal update: UCLA's police department concluded
its investigation into the disabled-parking scandal and forwarded
the information to city attorney Brian Williams on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   ``At this point we're evaluating the cases and no charges have
been filed,'' Williams said.
</P>
<P>
   Williams declined to name the players involved. However, the
UCLA police were known to be investigating current players Keith
Brown and Eric Whitfield, along with former players McNown, Atkins
and Skip Hicks. McNown has denied any wrongdoing.
</P>
<P>
   __ Brothers Bruin: The Bruins are recruiting three players'
younger brothers. Cornerback Lovell Houston's brother, Marcus, is
one of the top tailbacks in the nation. Defensive tackle Ken
Kocher's brother, Matt, is a 275-pound run stopper. And quarterback
Cory Paus' brother, Casey, is a 6-4, strong-armed passer entering
his junior year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-08-99 2328EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19990908.0417 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-08 23:30 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5400 &Cx1f; taf-z
